body:
@Suleman-Elahi looks like you have an older version of numpy. I bumped the minimum version required to 1.12.0; you should get it automatically if you do
`pip install git+https://github.com/smacke/subsync`
again. Let me know how it works after trying that and hopefully I can close the issue.

@postacik I think you're probably seeing this error because `ffmpeg-python` uses *nix pipes for IPC, and if that's the case I think it won't work for Windows. I'll create a feature request; unfortunately it will take me some time to get to this. I've opened #8 to track this.

@steven-kraft I see, interesting... it looks like my hypothesis about `ffmpeg-python` not working on Windows is (at least partially) false. The plot thickens.

I think the py-webrtcvad dependency requires compiling some C code into a python extension, which could partially explain why the MS visual C++ python compiler is necessary. Not sure why it's only needed for Python 2.7 though; perhaps Windows comes with it for Python 3.x? I'm unfortunately not very familiar with how Windows does things.

Probably I will need to grab a Windows VM to thoroughly investigate all the different possibilities in order to fix #8.
